				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$\sigma _{\mathrm{dark}}$\end{document}


						, calculated by taking the average standard deviation of all dark frames taken at each exposure time and polarization angle. It is clear that pixels in the detector follow the same pattern and behave uniformly across all polarization angles.

