Typically, similar studies and space-based coronagraphs use polarizer angles of 0
					∘, 60
					∘, and 120
					∘ to infer the coronal electron density. As mentioned previously, CIP is designed to efficiently take polarized observations for any number of predefined polarizer angles. For this study, six polarizer angles were chosen in an attempt to see if increasing the number of polarizer angles leads to better constraints on the



								pB

